t\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYnhQhDkScFhBSeQB8uR1\",\"uuid\":\"e43b853f-dd3a-4b37-91e3-1ff067199bb2\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a7d84148f339927d0\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_013NT5ERR5D9gWT8cYQfEhth\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_016zzTsWuoaopTTLDoNAx6Lp\",\"uuid\":\"332af885-6d58-4462-bfac-bbecb11b046c\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T23:30:52.308Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"332af885-6d58-4462-bfac-bbecb11b046c\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_019sreBakV6TxptBoRXe3bNt\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Sessions and Checkpoints\\n     2→\\n     3→## Overview\\n     4→\\n     5→Entire CLI creates checkpoints for AI coding sessions. The system is agent-agnostic - it works with Claude Code, Gemini CLI, OpenCode, Cursor, or any tool that triggers Entire hooks.\\n     6→\\n     7→## Domain Model\\n     8→\\n     9→### Session\\n    10→\\n    11→A **Session** is a unit of work. Defined in `strategy/session.go`:\\n    12→\\n    13→```go\\n    14→type Session struct {\\n    15→    ID          string       // e.g., \\\"2025-12-01-8f76b0e8-b8f1-4a87-9186-848bdd83d62e\\\"\\n    16→    Description string       // Human-readable summary (first prompt or derived)\\n    17→    Strategy    string       // Strategy that created this session\\n    18→    StartTime   time.Time\\n    19→    Checkpoints []Checkpoint\\n    20→}\\n    21→```\\n    22→\\n    23→### Checkpoint\\n    24→\\n    25→A **Checkpoint** captures a point-in-time within a session. Defined in `strategy/session.go`:\\n    26→\\n    27→```go\\n    28→type Checkpoint struct {\\n    29→    CheckpointID     id.CheckpointID // Stable 12-hex-char identifier\\n    30→    Message          string          // Commit message or checkpoint description\\n    31→    Timestamp        time.Time\\n    32→    IsTaskCheckpoint bool            // Task checkpoint (subagent) vs session checkpoint\\n    33→    ToolUseID        string          // Tool use ID for task checkpoints (empty for session)\\n    34→}\\n    35→```\\n    36→\\n    37→### Checkpoint Types\\n    38→\\n    39→The low-level `checkpoint.Type` (from `checkpoint/checkpoint.go`) indicates storage location:\\n    40→\\n    41→```go\\n    42→type Type int\\n    43→\\n    44→const (\\n    45→    Temporary Type = iota // Full state snapshot, shadow branch\\n    46→    Committed             // Metadata + commit ref, entire/checkpoints/v1\\n    47→)\\n    48→```\\n    49→\\n    50→| Type | Contents | Use Case |\\n    51→|------|----------|----------|\\n    52→| Temporary | Full state (code + metadata) | Intra-session rewind, pre-commit |\\n    53→| Committed | Metadata + commit reference | Permanent record, post-commit rewind |\\n    54→\\n    55→## Interface\\n    56→\\n    57→### Session Operations\\n    58→\\n    59→Sessions are accessed via standalone functions in `strategy/session.go`:\\n    60→\\n    61→```go\\n    62→// ListSessions returns all sessions from entire/checkpoints/v1,\\n    63→// plus additional sessions from strategies implementing SessionSource.\\n    64→func ListSessions() ([]Session, error)\\n    65→\\n    66→// GetSession finds a session by ID (supports prefix matching).\\n    67→func GetSession(sessionID string) (*Session, error)\\n    68→```\\n    69→\\n    70→### Checkpoint Storage (Low-Level)\\n    71→\\n    72→The `checkpoint.Store` interface (from `checkpoint/checkpoint.go`) provides primitives for reading/writing checkpoints. Used by strategies.\\n    73→\\n    74→```go\\n    75→type Store interface {\\n    76→    // Temporary checkpoint operations (shadow branches - full state)\\n    77→    WriteTemporary(ctx context.Context, opts WriteTemporaryOptions) (WriteTemporaryResult, error)\\n    78→    ReadTemporary(ctx context.Context, baseCommit, worktreeID string) (*ReadTemporaryResult, error)\\n    79→    ListTemporary(ctx context.Context) ([]TemporaryInfo, error)\\n    80→\\n    81→    // Committed checkpoint operations (entire/checkpoints/v1 branch - metadata only)\\n    82→    WriteCommitted(ctx context.Context, opts WriteCommittedOptions) error\\n    83→    ReadCommitted(ctx context.Context, checkpointID id.CheckpointID) (*CheckpointSummary, error)\\n    84→    ReadSessionContent(ctx context.Context, checkpointID id.CheckpointID, sessionIndex int) (*SessionContent, error)\\n    85→    ReadSessionContentByID(ctx context.Context, checkpointID id.CheckpointID, sessionID string) (*SessionContent, error)\\n    86→    ListCommitted(ctx context.Context) ([]CommittedInfo, error)\\n    87→}\\n    88→```\\n    89→\\n    90→Key option types (abbreviated):\\n    91→\\n    92→```go\\n    93→type WriteTemporaryOptions struct {\\n    94→    SessionID      string\\n    95→    BaseCommit     string\\n    96→    WorktreeID     string   // Internal git worktree identifier (empty for main)\\n    97→    ModifiedFiles  []string\\n    98→    NewFiles       []string\\n    99→    DeletedFiles   []string\\n   100→    MetadataDir    string   // Relative path to metadata directory\\n   101→    MetadataDirAbs string   // Absolute path\\n   102→    CommitMessage  string\\n   103→    // ...\\n   104→}\\n   105→\\n   106→type WriteCommittedOptions struct {\\n   107→    CheckpointID id.CheckpointID\\n   108→    SessionID    string\\n   109→    Strategy     string\\n   110→    Branch       string\\n   111→    Transcript   []byte\\n   112→    Prompts      []string\\n   113→    Context      []byte\\n   114→    FilesTouched []string\\n   115→    TokenUsage   *agent.TokenUsage\\n   116→    // ...\\n   117→}\\n   118→```\\n   119→\\n   120→Token usage is defined in `agent/types.go`:\\n   121→\\n   122→```go\\n   123→type TokenUsage struct {\\n   124→    InputTokens         int         `json:\\\"input_tokens\\\"`\\n   125→    CacheCreationTokens int         `json:\\\"cache_creation_tokens\\\"`\\n   126→    CacheReadTokens     int         `json:\\\"cache_read_tokens\\\"`\\n   127→    OutputTokens        int         `json:\\\"output_tokens\\\"`\\n   128→    APICallCount        int         `json:\\\"api_call_count\\\"`\\n   129→    SubagentTokens      *TokenUsage `json:\\\"subagent_tokens,omitempty\\\"`\\n   130→}\\n   131→```\\n   132→\\n   133→### Strategy-Level Operations\\n   134→\\n   135→Strategies compose low-level primitives into higher-level workflows.\\n   136→\\n   137→**Manual-commit** has condensation logic:\\n   138→\\n   139→```go\\n   140→// CondenseSession reads accumulated temporary state and writes a committed checkpoint.\\n   141→func (s *ManualCommitStrategy) CondenseSession(\\n   142→    repo *git.Repository,\\n   143→    checkpointID id.CheckpointID,\\n   144→    state *SessionState,\\n   145→) (*CondenseResult, error)\\n   146→```\\n   147→\\n   148→## Storage\\n   149→\\n   150→| Type | Location | Contents |\\n   151→|------|----------|----------|\\n   152→| Session State | `.git/entire-sessions/<id>.json` | Active session tracking |\\n   153→| Temporary | `entire/<commit[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>` branch | Full state (code + metadata) |\\n   154→| Committed | `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch (sharded) | Metadata + commit reference |\\n   155→\\n   156→### Session State\\n   157→\\n   158→Location: `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json`\\n   159→\\n   160→Stored in git common dir (shared across worktrees). Tracks active session info.\\n   161→\\n   162→### Temporary Checkpoints\\n   163→\\n   164→Branch: `entire/<commit[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>`\\n   165→\\n   166→Contains full worktree snapshot plus metadata overlay. **Multiple concurrent sessions** can share the same shadow branch - their checkpoints interleave:\\n   167→\\n   168→```\\n   169→<worktree files...>\\n   170→.entire/metadata/<session-id-1>/\\n   171→├── full.jsonl           # Session 1 transcript\\n   172→├── prompt.txt           # Checkpoint-scoped user prompts\\n   173→└── tasks/<tool-use-id>/ # Task checkpoints\\n   174→.entire/metadata/<session-id-2>/\\n   175→├── full.jsonl           # Session 2 transcript (concurrent)\\n   176→├── ...\\n   177→```\\n   178→\\n   179→Tied to a base commit. Condensed to committed on user commit.\\n   180→\\n   181→**Shadow branch lifecycle:**\\n   182→- Created on first checkpoint for a base commit\\n   183→- Migrated automatically if base commit changes (stash → pull → apply scenario)\\n   184→- Deleted after condensation to `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n   185→- Reset if orphaned (no session state file exists)\\n   186→\\n   187→### Committed Checkpoints\\n   188→\\n   189→Branch: `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n   190→\\n   191→Metadata only, sharded by checkpoint ID. Supports **multiple sessions per checkpoint**:\\n   192→\\n   193→```\\n   194→<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/\\n   195→├── metadata.json        # CheckpointSummary (aggregated stats)\\n   196→├── 0/                   # First session (0-based indexing)\\n   197→│   ├── metadata.json    # Session-specific CommittedMetadata\\n   198→│   ├── full.jsonl\\n   199→│   ├── prompt.txt       # Checkpoint-scoped user prompts\\n   200→│   └── content_hash.txt\"}]},\"uuid\":\"f1f3f820-7339-4300-8af7-8ced78c5139e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T23:30:52.318Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a7d84148f339927d0\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_013NT5ERR5D9gWT8cYQfEhth\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_016zzTsWuoaopTTLDoNAx6Lp\",\"uuid\":\"66dfad14-fb31-4f1b-841b-74f9ef8b09c6\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T23:30:52.318Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"66dfad14-fb31-4f1b-841b-74f9ef8b09c6\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Agent\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code post-task\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_016zzTsWuoaopTTLDoNAx6Lp\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_016zzTsWuoaopTTLDoNAx6Lp\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T23:31:18.056Z\",\"uuid\":\"f65f9da1-2d89-459e-b567-feac0e294f37\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"56ac4f31-5dbe-418d-9dd9-e6ade68a4028\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_016zzTsWuoaopTTLDoNAx6Lp\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me compile my findings into a detailed report.\\n\\n## Summary of Findings\\n\\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's what I've discovered about the current architecture and how **trails** fit into it:\\n\\n### Current Architecture Overview\\n\\n#### 1. **Shadow Branches** (Temporary Checkpoints)\\n- **Naming**: `entire/<commit[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>`\\n  - First 7 characters of the base commit hash\\n  - Plus a 6-character hash of the worktree ID (empty string for main worktree)\\n  - Example: `entire/a3b2c4d-5e6f7a` (where `5e6f7a` = hash of worktreeID)\\n- **Purpose**: Store full session state (code + metadata) during an active session\\n- **Lifecycle**:\\n  - Created on first checkpoint for a base commit\\n  - Automatically migrated if HEAD changes (rebase/pull scenario)\\n  - Deleted after condensation to metadata branch\\n  - Reset if orphaned (no corresponding session state file)\\n- **Scoping**: Each git worktree gets its own shadow branch namespace (worktree-specific naming)\\n- **Multi-session support**: Checkpoints from different concurrent sessions interleave on the same shadow branch\\n\\n#### 2. **Session State** (`.git/entire-sessions/`)\\n- **Location**: `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json`\\n- **Scope**: Shared across worktrees (stored in git common dir)\\n- **Tracks**:\\n  - `BaseCommit`: Current shadow branch base (updated on HEAD change/migration)\\n  - `AttributionBaseCommit`: Original base for attribution calculations\\n  - `WorktreeID`: Internal git worktree identifier (empty for main)\\n  - `Phase`: Session lifecycle (IDLE, ACTIVE, ENDED)\\n  - `SessionID`: Unique session identifier\\n  - `FilesTouched`: Accumulated files modified in this session\\n  - Plus transcript position, token usage, turn tracking, etc.\\n\\n#### 3. **Metadata Branch** (`entire/checkpoints/v1`)\\n- **Purpose**: Permanent storage of session metadata\\n- **Structure**: Sharded by checkpoint ID (first 2 chars = shard, rest = suffix)\\n  - Path: `a3/b2c4d5e6f7/` for checkpoint ID `a3b2c4d5e6f7`\\n- **Multi-session support**: Multiple sessions can be condensed to the same checkpoint\\n  - Stored in numbered subfolders (`0/`, `1/`, `2/`, etc.)\\n  - Each session gets its own metadata.json + full.jsonl\\n- **Contents per session**:\\n  - `metadata.json` (session-specific CommittedMetadata)\\n  - `full.jsonl` (transcript)\\n  - `prompt.txt` (checkpoint-scoped prompts)\\n  - `tasks/<tool-use-id>/` (task checkpoints for subagents)\\n\\n#### 4. **Trails** (Branch-Centric Work Tracking)\\n- **Orphan Branch**: `entire/trails/v1`\\n- **Purpose**: Answer \\\"why/what\\\" while checkpoints answer \\\"how/when\\\"\\n- **Storage Structure**: Sharded like checkpoints\\n  - Path: `a3/b2c4d5e6f7/` for trail ID `a3b2c4d5e6f7`\\n- **Per-Trail Files**:\\n  - `metadata.json` (TrailMetadata)\\n  - `discussion.json` (comments/discussion)\\n  - `checkpoints.json` (list of checkpoint references)\\n- **Branch-to-Trail Mapping**:\\n  - Each trail has a `Branch` field (e.g., `feature/auth`)\\n  - `Base` field (base branch, e.g., `main`)\\n  - `FindByBranch()` looks up trail by working branch name\\n- **Checkpoint Linking**:\\n  - Trails maintain a list of `CheckpointRef` (checkpoint ID + commit SHA + summary)\\n  - When a commit is condensed, checkpoint is appended to matching trail\\n  - Logic in `manual_commit_hooks.go:1100-1108`:\\n    - Gets current branch name\\n    - Finds trail for that branch via `store.FindByBranch(branchName)`\\n    - If found and on non-default branch, appends checkpoint to trail's checkpoints list\\n\\n#### 5. **Session Lifecycle**\\n- **Phase State Machine** (`session/phase.go`):\\n  - IDLE → ACTIVE (on TurnStart)\\n  - ACTIVE → IDLE (on TurnEnd)\\n  - ACTIVE → ENDED (on SessionStop)\\n  - ENDED → ACTIVE/IDLE (on reactivation or new prompt)\\n- **Worktree-Scoped**: Sessions don't directly reference branches, but:\\n  - Shadow branches are worktree-specific\\n  - Session state is shared across worktrees\\n  - When switching worktrees/branches, a new shadow branch is created for the new base commit\\n\\n### Key Architectural Patterns\\n\\n#### Branch Awareness\\n- **Session is NOT branch-aware**: A session is tied to a base commit, not a branch\\n- **Trails ARE branch-aware**: Each trail is linked to a specific branch\\n- **Shadow branches are commit-aware**: Named by commit hash + worktree ID\\n- **When user switches branches**:\\n  - Same session continues (session ID stays the same)\\n  - Shadow branch is migrated to new base commit if HEAD changed\\n  - Trail lookup uses current branch name at checkpoint creation time\\n\\n#### Multi-Branch Scenarios (Current Limitations)\\n- **Single session per worktree**: Only one session can be ACTIVE at a time per directory\\n- **Multi-session support exists**: Multiple IDLE/ENDED sessions can coexist\\n- **Concurrent sessions in same directory**: Possible but warned about\\n  - Both sessions can proceed\\n  - Checkpoints interleave on same shadow branch\\n  - On commit, all sessions condensed together with archived sessions in numbered subfolders\\n- **Different worktrees**: Each worktree can have its own session (different shadow branch names)\\n- **Branch switching**: No automatic session management\\n  - User must manually track which session is which\\n  - Trails help organize work by branch\\n\\n#### No Native \\\"Stacked PR\\\" or \\\"Multi-Branch Session\\\" Support\\n- **Currently**: Each session/trail is single-branch\\n- **Worktree as proxy**: Users can use git worktrees to work on multiple branches \\\"simultaneously\\\"\\n  - Each worktree gets its own shadow branch\\n  - Each worktree gets its own session (different `.git/entire-sessions/<id>.json`)\\n  - Sessions share the metadata branch but not state files\\n\\n### Integration Points\\n\\n#### Checkpoints ↔ Trails Linkage\\n- **One-way link**: Trails know about checkpoints (via `checkpoints.json`)\\n- **Automatic**: When a commit is condensed:\\n  1. Current branch name is determined\\n  2. Trail lookup by branch name\\n  3. If found (and not default branch), checkpoint added to trail's checkpoints list\\n  4. Call: `appendCheckpointToExistingTrail(store, existing.TrailID, result.CheckpointID, head.Hash(), result.Prompts)`\\n\\n#### User Prompt ↔ Branch Association\\n- **Trail Metadata**: Stores `Title`, `Body`, `Status`, `Author`, etc.\\n- **First prompt**: Implicitly captured in trail creation (via `entire trail create` command)\\n- **Checkpoint prompts**: Stored in trail's checkpoints as summaries (first line of latest prompt)\\n\\n### Files & Locations to Understand\\n\\n**Key Implementation Files**:\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/trail/trail.go` - Trail domain model\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/trail/store.go` - Trail CRUD operations\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/trail_cmd.go` - CLI commands for trails\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` - Post-commit trail linking (lines 1100-1108, 2374-2390)\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_git.go` 