.834Z\"},\"isSnapshotUpdate\":false}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"716d02aa-659c-4ea0-95d7-04624cab0007\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"1. the ux is a bit clunky, we currently 'auto-generate' a branch name but you can go back and edit it\\n2. perhaps `entire trail branch add` adds this branch? I don't know how to avoid adding branches into multiple trails by accident though 😅 (maybe doesn't matter for now). We should also have a version where we can pass the branch.\"},\"uuid\":\"e8de6244-ee1d-4ba7-ac1d-66f8685ce51c\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T23:47:43.107Z\",\"permissionMode\":\"default\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"e8de6244-ee1d-4ba7-ac1d-66f8685ce51c\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01ComkvJdfPi76kFeyKb4Svy\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Okay, so let me understand:\\n\\n1. On `trail create`, a branch name is auto-generated, but editable. The current branch is implicitly the first branch entry.\\n\\n2. `entire trail branch add` (no args) adds the current branch to the trail. But also support `entire trail branch add <branch-name>` for explicit specification.\\n\\nThe concern about accidentally adding a branch to multiple trails is real but they say maybe doesn't matter for now. We could validate/warn but not block.\\n\\nI think I have enough context to propose approaches now. Let me think about what the 2-3 approaches are.\\n\\nActually, let me think about one more thing - how does this interact with the existing checkpoint flow? When a commit happens on a branch, the post-commit hook currently:\\n\\n\\n1. Gets the current branch name\\n2. Finds the trail by branch name via `store.FindByBranch(branchName)`\\n3. If found, appends checkpoint to trail\\n\\nWith multi-branch trails, the lookup changes from \\\"find trail by its single Branch field\\\" to \\\"find trail that has a branch entry matching the current branch.\\\" This is a storage/query concern.\\n\\nI also need to think about the data model changes needed on the `entire/trails/v1` branch. The current TrailMetadata has TrailID, Title, Body, Status, Priority, Type, Branch, Base (single values), Author, Reviewers, CreatedAt, UpdatedAt. I'll need to refactor this to support multiple branches instead of a single Branch field.\\n\\nThe new model replaces Branch and Base with a Branches array containing BranchEntry objects, each with an ID, Name, BaseBranch, BaseCommit, optional PR, Checkpoints, and AddedAt timestamp. Now I'm thinking through the migration approaches—the first option is to evolve the Trail in-place by adding the Branches array, migrating existing Branch/Base data to the first entry, and updating FindByBranch to scan across all trails.\\n\\nThe second approach separates concerns by keeping trails lean and creating a branch registry index that maps branch names to trail IDs, with branch entries stored in separate files per trail. The third approach stores each branch entry as its own directory in the trail's git tree, keeping trail metadata minimal while organizing branch details hierarchically.\\n\\nI'm leaning toward Approach 1 for simplicity, but I need to think through backward compatibility with the existing trail structure. The current layout stores metadata, discussion, and checkpoints at the trail level, so with multi-branch support, checkpoints need to move somewhere—either as a flat list with a BranchID field, organized under a branches directory, or embedded directly in the branch entry within metadata.json. Embedding them in the branch entry seems cleanest.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1124,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":35656,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1124},\"output_tokens\":6,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYnihQsafhqAGuT16SFWK\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"a6947595-38d3-405a-b066-c9399f5e1089\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T23:48:07.830Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"a6947595-38d3-405a-b066-c9399f5e1089\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01ComkvJdfPi76kFeyKb4Svy\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Makes sense. And yeah, a warning if a branch is already in another trail is probably sufficient — no need to hard-block.\\n\\nI think I have enough context to propose approaches. Let me lay them out.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Three Approaches\\n\\n### Approach A: Evolve TrailMetadata in-place (Recommended)\\n\\nAdd `Branches []BranchEntry` to `TrailMetadata`, migrate existing `Branch`/`Base` into the first entry. Checkpoints move from trail-level (`checkpoints.json`) to per-branch-entry.\\n\\n```\\nTrailMetadata {\\n  TrailID, Title, Body, Status, ...\\n  Branches: []BranchEntry          // replaces Branch + Base\\n}\\n\\nBranchEntry {\\n  ID:          \\\"uuid\\\"\\n  Name:        \\\"alex/auth-refactor\\\"\\n  BaseBranch:  \\\"main\\\"\\n  BaseCommit:  \\\"abc1234...\\\"        // fork point, updated on rebase\\n  PR:          *PRRef              // optional {Number, URL, Status}\\n  Checkpoints: []CheckpointRef\\n  AddedAt:     timestamp\\n}\\n```\\n\\nStorage stays the same (single `metadata.json` per trail). `FindByBranch` scans all trails' branch entries — fine at our scale.\\n\\n**Pros:** Simple, single file per trail, easy migration, minimal new plumbing.\\n**Cons:** `FindByBranch` is O(trails × branches) — acceptable for now.\\n\\n### Approach B: Separate branch index file\\n\\nKeep `metadata.json` lean. Add `branches.json` to each trail's tree with the branch entries. Plus a global `branch-index.json` mapping branch names → trail IDs for fast lookup.\\n\\n**Pros:** Fast O(1) branch lookup, cleaner separation.\\n**Cons:** Two files to keep in sync, index can go stale, more git tree operations per update.\\n\\n### Approach C: Branch entries as subdirectories\\n\\nEach branch gets its own directory: `<trail-shard>/branches/<branch-id>/metadata.json`.\\n\\n**Pros:** Independently updatable, scales to many branches.\\n**Cons:** Overkill complexity for a flat list of ~2-5 entries per trail.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**My recommendation: Approach A.** The number of branches per trail will be small (typically 1-5), the number of trails per repo will be modest, and the single-file-per-trail simplicity is worth the O(n) scan. We can add an index later if it becomes a bottleneck.\\n\\nWhat do you think?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1124,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":35656,\"output_tokens\":1580,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1124,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYnihQsafhqAGuT16SFWK\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"46403127-70f3-4005-a1a4-5d02d0db7422\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T23:48:16.999Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"46403127-70f3-4005-a1a4-5d02d0db7422\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"us