ail (canary, rollout), some could be either (security review could be per-PR or per-trail).\\n\\nThe event log model handles this naturally. Each event has a `kind`, optional `branch_id` (for branch-scoped verifications), status, timestamp, and details.\\n\\nI think we've aligned on the data model. \\n\\nNow I'll consolidate the full model and move forward with the migration strategy, CLI commands, and how the hooks integrate with everything.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":769,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":51673,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":769},\"output_tokens\":8,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYnmGTVVnDC7SJnpmgnP1\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"40eb8e34-98d5-4c6b-a165-9ef73607301d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:21:32.302Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"40eb8e34-98d5-4c6b-a165-9ef73607301d\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01X5KhFumazjnPpQ4KP1yM9K\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Exactly. Verification is a unified concept with many kinds — all the same shape, just different scopes and triggers:\\n\\n| Kind | Scope | Trigger |\\n|------|-------|---------|\\n| PR checks (CI) | per-branch | automated |\\n| Code review / approval | per-branch | human |\\n| Security review | per-branch or per-trail | human |\\n| Performance review | per-branch or per-trail | human/automated |\\n| Canary | per-trail | automated |\\n| Rollout stage | per-trail | automated |\\n| Post-deploy monitoring | per-trail | automated |\\n\\nThe model handles all of these uniformly. Let me consolidate the full data model and move on.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Consolidated Data Model (revised)\\n\\n```\\nTrail\\n+-- title              (human-friendly label)\\n+-- status             (draft → open → in_progress → in_review → merged → deploying → deployed | rolled_back)\\n+-- intent\\n+--   kind             (file, url, issue, inline)\\n+--   value            (path, URL, issue ID, inline text)\\n+--   content          (resolved/cached text)\\n+--   amendments[]\\n+--     description\\n+--     reasoning\\n+--     timestamp\\n+-- branches[]\\n+--   id               (stable UUID)\\n+--   name             (branch ref, informational)\\n+--   base_branch      (target branch name)\\n+--   base_commit      (fork point SHA)\\n+--   status           (open, merged, discarded)\\n+--   pr               (optional, replaceable: number, url)\\n+-- checkpoints[]      (the spine)\\n+--   checkpoint_id, commit_sha, summary\\n+--   branch_id        (links to branch entry)\\n+--   sessions[]\\n+-- verification[]     (event log — unified across all verification types)\\n+--   kind             (pr_checks, review, security, perf, canary, rollout_stage, ...)\\n+--   branch_id        (optional — per-branch or per-trail)\\n+--   status           (pass, fail, pending)\\n+--   timestamp\\n+--   details\\n+-- discussion[]       (separate file)\\n+-- summary            (aggregated)\\n```\\n\\n**Storage on `entire/trails/v1`:**\\n```\\n<shard>/<suffix>/\\n├── metadata.json      (title, status, intent, branches, summary)\\n├── checkpoints.json   (checkpoint refs with branch_id)\\n├── verification.json  (verification event log — NEW file)\\n└── discussion.json    (comments/threads)\\n```\\n\\nVerification gets its own file since it grows independently and could get large (automated events accumulate).\\n\\n---\\n\\nDoes this consolidated model look right? If so I'll move on to migration and CLI commands.\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_to