"type\":\"file-history-snapshot\",\"messageId\":\"0405d622-1da5-415e-a17d-e7b5f7e8bffb\",\"snapshot\":{\"messageId\":\"0405d622-1da5-415e-a17d-e7b5f7e8bffb\",\"trackedFileBackups\":{},\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:24:57.608Z\"},\"isSnapshotUpdate\":false}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"58dd60f2-a2df-405b-ad42-1141b12fef06\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"do we need to have the status delineation between in_review -> merged -> deploying -> deployed -> done?\\n\\na progressive rollout strategy could be modelled as either the tail of the review process or a 'validating' stage? Do we need to know the underlying mechanics of it?\"},\"uuid\":\"0405d622-1da5-415e-a17d-e7b5f7e8bffb\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:24:56.803Z\",\"permissionMode\":\"default\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"0405d622-1da5-415e-a17d-e7b5f7e8bffb\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01466c8KziRyv7Vie5qz3EED\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Good point. The user is pushing back on the granularity of the status field. They're saying we don't need to model the deployment pipeline stages in the trail status — that's what the verification event log is for. The trail just needs to know high-level phases.\\n\\nLet me think about this:\\n- `in_review` → `merged` → `deploying` → `deployed` is very prescriptive about the deployment pipeline\\n- The verification event log already captures the detailed stages (canary pass, rollout 10%, rollout 50%, etc.)\\n- The trail status should reflect the *intent lifecycle*, not the deployment mechanics\\n\\nSo maybe:\\n- `draft` → `active` → `in_review` → `done` (or `closed`)\\n\\n\\n- With `in_review` covering everything from \\\"PRs are up for review\\\" through \\\"validating in production\\\"\\n- The verification events tell you the details of where in the review/validation process you are\\n\\nOr even simpler: `draft` → `active` → `validating` → `done`, where `validating` encompasses both code review and post-merge verification. The trail is either being worked on, being validated, or done.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":918,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":52442,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":918},\"output_tokens\":8,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYnmY5f2yMKsTJ6g8pkDB\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"3fd249bb-7e79-4d81-9ba5-1829fb4eea1d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:25:08.275Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"3fd249bb-7e79-4d81-9ba5-1829fb4eea1d\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01466c8KziRyv7Vie5qz3EED\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"You're right — the verification event log already captures the mechanics. The trail status shouldn't duplicate that. It should reflect the *intent lifecycle*, not the deployment pipeline.\\n\\nSimpler:\\n\\n```\\ndraft → active → validating → done\\n                     ↓\\n                  abandoned\\n```\\n\\n- **draft** — intent defined, work hasn't started\\n- **active** — branches exist, work in progress\\n- **validating** — PRs up for review, canary running, rollout in progress — all \\\"is this good?\\\" activity\\n- **done** — intent fully realized and verified\\n- **abandoned** — intent dropped\\n\\nWhether you're waiting on a code review or at 50% canary rollout, the trail is \\\"validating.\\\" The verification event log tells you *what kind* of validation and *where* in the process. The trail status just says \\\"we think we're done, checking.\\\"\\n\\nThis also avoids the problem of status transitions being tightly coupled to a specific deployment model — not every trail goes through canary/rollout.\\n\\nDoes this feel right?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":918,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":52442,\"output_tokens\":560,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":918,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYnmY5f2yMKsTJ6g8pkDB\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"0def4d24-1b40-4771-9ba0-847e3d665912\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:25:12.548Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"0def4d24-1b40-4771-9ba0-847e3d665912\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"93b4a0b1-9ab7-4ee6-bef1-0abea8f50d3e\",\"toolUseID\":\"93b4a0b1-9ab7-4ee6-bef1-0abea8f50d3e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:25:12.551Z\",\"uuid\":\"299cddcf-1028-4248-b477-9f94c2e44f66\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"299cddcf-1028-4248-b477-9f94c2e44f66\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"stop_hook_summary\",\"hookCount\":1,\"hookInfos\":[{\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\",\"durationMs\":551}],\"hookErrors\":[],\"preventedContinuation\":false,\"stopReason\":\"\",\"hasOutput\":false,\"level\":\"suggestion\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:25:13.102Z\",\"uuid\":\"d24a0883-525c-4f00-9fe5-1a2ae3e9936a\",\"toolUseID\":\"93b4a0b1-9ab7-4ee6-bef1-0abea8f50d3e\"}\n{\"type\":\"file-history-snapshot\",\"messageId\":\"9f484420-5440-4b9b-892c-ca0060262d36\",\"snapshot\":{\"messageId\":\"9f484420-5440-4b9b-892c-ca0060262d36\",\"trackedFileBackups\":{},\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:26:44.079Z\"},\"isSnapshotUpdate\":false}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"d24a0883-525c-4f00-9fe5-1a2ae3e9936a\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"the only reason I'd keep something in there is if there needs to be a specific trigger for human action, i.e. the \\\"Trail Review\\\".\\n\\nThat said it that activity could happen at various points in the process and is perhaps a different type of Verification in itself...\"},\"uuid\":\"9f484420-5440-4b9b-892c-ca0060262d36\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:26:43.252Z\",\"permissionMode\":\"default\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"9f484420-5440-4b9b-892c-ca0060262d36\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01VxzHpCb4qYgWTQD8WV6LA2\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\nYeah — a \\\"Trail Review\\\" is a verification event, not a status. It could happen at different points:\\n\\n- Before any PRs are merged (design review)\\n- After first PR lands but before the rest (checkpoint review)\\n- After all code lands but before rollout (final review)\\n\\nIf it's a status, you're forced into one spot in the lifecycle. If it's a verification event, it can happen whenever it's needed — and the trail just stays `validating`.\\n\\nThe trigger for human action could come from the verification log itself: \\\"all automated checks passed, no `trail_review` event yet → surface a prompt to the user.\\\" That's a policy decision on top of the data, not baked into the state machine.\\n\\nSo I'd keep the simple statuses:\\n\\n```\\ndraft → active → validating → done | abandoned\\n```\\n\\nAnd model trail review as:\\n\\n```\\nverification event:\\n  kind: \\\"trail_review\\\"\\n  status: \\\"requested\\\" | \\\"approved\\\" | \\\"changes_requested\\\"\\n  branch_id: optional (could be trail-wide or per-branch)\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\nReady to move on to migration and CLI commands?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":616,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":53360,\"output_tokens\":260,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":616,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYnmfvohVz1ZcYw6YeuGo\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"31c38928-328b-41f0-acda-c2d5b1606ccc\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:26:53.043Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"31c38928-328b-41f0-acd