 trail context, we want per-worktree state.\\n \\nSo I have a few options: store trail context in the worktree-specific git directory, in a `.entire/` folder within the working directory itself, or in the shared directory but keyed by worktree ID. The key insight is that I need to use the resolved git directory path rather than assuming `.git` is a directory. The codebase already has the utilities to handle this with `paths.WorktreeRoot()` and worktree ID tracking.\\n\\nSince trail context is per-worktree, I should store it in the worktree-specific git directory rather than the common one, or alternatively use `.entire/` in the working directory.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":627,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":54942,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":627},\"output_tokens\":8,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYnn4estMMgvqf2PZjgV9\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"27f8be29-5f04-4130-91b2-4fddb3f83ff2\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:32:03.374Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"27f8be29-5f04-4130-91b2-4fddb3f83ff2\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_015GXA6Pymjf42QCQdo8Uudm\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Right — in a linked worktree, `.git` is a file containing `gitdir: /path/to/main/.git/worktrees/<name>/`, not a directory.\\n\\nTwo relevant paths:\\n- **`git rev-parse --git-dir`** → worktree-specific: `/main/.git/worktrees/<name>/` \\n- **`git rev-parse --git-common-dir`** → shared: `/main/.git/`\\n\\nSession state already lives in the common dir (`.git/entire-sessions/`). But trail context is per-worktree, so options:\\n\\n1. **Worktree-specific git dir** — `<git-dir>/entire-trail-context` (e.g., `/main/.git/worktrees/auth/entire-trail-context`). Git-native, invisible to the working tree.\\n\\n2. **`.entire/` in the working directory** — already exists per worktree, already gitignored. Simplest to find.\\n\\n3. **Common dir, keyed by worktree ID** — like sessions do today, but with worktree scoping.\\n\\nI'd lean toward **(2)** — `.entire/trail-context.json` in the working directory. It's where all other Entire local state lives, it's already gitignored, and it works identically in both main worktrees and linked worktrees without resolving git dir paths.\\n\\nDoes that work?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":627,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":54942,\"output_tokens\":761,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":627,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYnn4estMMgvqf2PZjgV9\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"a50a68a2-6060-4533-91fb-53f8cca57754\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:32:08.889Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"a50a68a2-6060-4533-91fb-53f8cca57754\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"3b8d4eeb-c34d-4044-86ec-9556e03f7553\",\"toolUseID\":\"3b8d4eeb-c34d-4044-86ec-9556e03f7553\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:32:08.892Z\",\"uuid\":