,\"id\":\"msg_01CW4Ca2Sn7fcoPbwezBh5dU\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Ah, the user is pointing out a problem. If we store the active trail context in `.entire/trail-context.json` in the working directory, it persists when the user switches branches within the same worktree. So:\\n\\n1. User is on `feature/auth-core`, active trail is Trail A\\n2. User does `git checkout main` \\n3. `.entire/trail-context.json` still says Trail A is active\\n4. User does `entire trail branch add` — oops, adds `main` to Trail A?\\n\\nThe stored context becomes stale/wrong when branches change. This is the classic problem with local state that's tied to a branch.\\n\\n\\nI'm weighing a few approaches here. We could skip storing context entirely and always look up the branch in our trail mappings, but that breaks when a branch isn't tracked yet. Or we could store the context but validate it each time—check if the current branch actually belongs to the active trail and warn if it doesn't. There's also the git hook angle with `post-checkout`, though that's unreliable for `git switch`. But the most promising option is storing context per-branch instead of just a single active trail—mapping each branch to its trail so branch switches naturally resolve the right context.\\n\\nThat said, storing a branch-to-trail mapping duplicates what's already in the trail metadata itself. So maybe the cleanest solution is to always derive context from a branch lookup with an explicit override fallback: check for a `--trail` flag first, then scan for the current branch in existing trails, and if nothing matches, prompt the user. This avoids stale context entirely—the only cost is a branch scan on each command, which is fine at our scale. The trade-off is that new branches not yet added to a trail require explicit specification, but that's actually reasonable behavior.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":779,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":55569,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":779},\"output_tokens\":6,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYnn9eXgznHtLSG7Z44zV\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"e523cb63-a80d-4fc6-9434-d4c76e064062\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:33:16.298Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"e523cb63-a80d-4fc6-9434-d4c76e064062\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01CW4Ca2Sn7fcoPbwezBh5dU\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Yeah, that's the problem with stored context — it goes stale on `git checkout`. And there's no reliable hook for branch switches.\\n\\nMaybe we don't store context at all. Just derive it:\\n\\n1. **`--trail <id>` flag** — explicit, always wins\\n2. **Branch→trail lookup** — current branch found in exactly one trail\\n3. **No match** → prompt/error\\n\\nThe \\\"cost\\\" is a branch→trail scan on every command, but we said that's fine at our scale. And it's always correct — no stale state to worry about.\\n\\nThe one gap: you're on a new branch that hasn't been added to any trail yet. But that's actually the right moment to be explicit — you're either:\\n- `entire trail create` (new trail, branch auto-added)\\n- `entire trail branch add` (needs to know which trail → `--trail <id>` or interactive picker if few trails are active)\\n\\nOnce the branch is in a trail, all subsequent commands auto-resolve.\\n\\nThis is simpler, stateless, and branch-switch-proof. The tradeoff is that `entire trail branch add` on a fresh branch needs trail disambiguation, but that's a one-time action per branch.\\n\\nDoes stateless lookup feel sufficient, or do you think there are commands where it falls short?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":779,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":55569,\"output_tokens\":834,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":779,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYnn9eXgznHtLSG7Z44zV\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"c4fbfe39-00be-45df-8a05-3a31fc11031e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:33:20.057Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c4fbfe39-00be-45df-8a05-3a31fc11031e\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"58636a2a-dbeb-4535-b79a-a4a516a2ecb0\",\"toolUseID\":\"58636a2a-dbeb-4535-b79a-a4a516a2ecb0\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:33:20.084Z\",\"uuid\":\"6afcada8-107e-4e0e-ac6a-488c662116f0\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"6afcada8-107e-4e0e-ac6a-488c662116f0\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"stop_hook_summary\",\"hookCount\":1,\"hookInfos\":[{\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\",\"durationMs\":607}],\"hookErrors\":[],\"preventedContinuation\":false,\"stopReason\":\"\",\"hasO