nt_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a90079da00a244817\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01KBGzztDAkNnBXL2Qi26Q4g\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01Y7spufBycXcSrMdgWWWZGf\",\"uuid\":\"e2fffe00-a956-4ef8-aa05-410de6d8166e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:38:02.409Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"e2fffe00-a956-4ef8-aa05-410de6d8166e\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Rk3WEZQnhQWyRKJXQaTNZe\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Trails: Multi-Branch & Multi-PR Support\\n     2→\\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-07\\n     4→**Status:** Draft\\n     5→\\n     6→## Problem\\n     7→\\n     8→Trails currently model a 1:1 relationship between a trail and a branch. Real work\\n     9→often spans multiple branches and PRs: stacked PRs for large features, iterative\\n    10→follow-up PRs, or parallel refactor-then-feature splits. The trail should represent\\n    11→the *intent*, with branches/PRs as execution artifacts serving that intent.\\n    12→\\n    13→## Design Principles\\n    14→\\n    15→- **Trail = intent.** Branches and PRs are mutable execution details.\\n    16→- **Flat list of branches.** No dependency graph — git already encodes branch topology.\\n    17→- **Stateless lookup.** Active trail resolved from current branch, not stored context.\\n    18→- **CAS for concurrency.** Optimistic retry on ref updates, not file splitting.\\n    19→- **Extensible verification.** Unified event log for all verification types.\\n    20→\\n    21→## Data Model\\n    22→\\n    23→### Trail (top-level)\\n    24→\\n    25→```\\n    26→Trail\\n    27→+-- title              (human-friendly label for display)\\n    28→+-- status             (draft | active | validating | done | abandoned)\\n    29→+-- intent             (typed reference — the \\\"what and why\\\")\\n    30→+--   kind             (file, url, issue, inline)\\n    31→+--   value            (path, URL, issue ID, inline text)\\n    32→+--   content          (resolved/cached text)\\n    33→+--   amendments[]     (spec changes with reasoning)\\n    34→+--     description\\n    35→+--     reasoning\\n    36→+--     timestamp\\n    37→+-- branches[]         (execution artifacts — the \\\"how\\\")\\n    38→+--   id               (stable UUID)\\n    39→+--   name             (branch ref, informational — may go stale)\\n    40→+--   base_branch      (target branch name, e.g. \\\"main\\\")\\n    41→+--   base_commit      (fork point SHA, updated on rebase)\\n    42→+--   status           (open | merged | discarded)\\n    43→+--   pr               (optional, replaceable)\\n    44→+--     number\\n    45→+--     url\\n    46→+-- checkpoints[]      (the spine — the \\\"when\\\")\\n    47→+--   checkpoint_id\\n    48→+--   commit_sha\\n    49→+--   summary\\n    50→+--   branch_id        (links to BranchEntry.ID)\\n    51→+--   sessions[]       (contributing agent sessions)\\n    52→+-- verification[]     (event log — unified across all verification types)\\n    53→+--   kind             (pr_checks, review, security, perf, canary,\\n    54→+--                     rollout_stage, trail_review, ...)\\n    55→+--   branch_id        (optional — per-branch or per-trail)\\n    56→+--   status           (pass, fail, pending, requested, approved,\\n    57→+--                     changes_requested)\\n    58→+--   timestamp\\n    59→+--   details\\n    60→+-- discussion[]       (comments/threads — separate file)\\n    61→+-- summary            (aggregated trail-level summary)\\n    62→```\\n    63→\\n    64→### Intent (typed reference)\\n    65→\\n    66→```go\\n    67→type Intent struct {\\n    68→    Kind       string      `json:\\\"kind\\\"`                // file, url, issue, inline\\n    69→    Value      string      `json:\\\"value\\\"`               // path, URL, issue ID, inline text\\n    70→    Content    string      `json:\\\"content,omitempty\\\"`    // resolved intent text (cached)\\n    71→    Amendments []Amendment `json:\\\"amendments,omitempty\\\"`\\n    72→}\\n    73→\\n    74→type Amendment struct {\\n    75→    Description string    `json:\\\"description\\\"`\\n    76→    Reasoning   string    `json:\\\"reasoning\\\"`\\n    77→    Timestamp   time.Time `json:\\\"timestamp\\\"`\\n    78→}\\n    79→```\\n    80→\\n    81→### BranchEntry\\n    82→\\n    83→```go\\n    84→type BranchEntry struct {\\n    85→    ID         string       `json:\\\"id\\\"`                  // stable UUID\\n    86→    Name       string       `json:\\\"name\\\"`                // branch name (informational, may go stale)\\n    87→    BaseBranch string       `json:\\\"base_branch\\\"`         // target branch name\\n    88→    BaseCommit string       `json:\\\"base_commit\\\"`         // fork point SHA\\n    89→    Status     BranchStatus `json:\\\"status\\\"`              // open, merged, discarded\\n    90→    PR         *PRRef       `json:\\\"pr,omitempty\\\"`        // optional, replaceable\\n    91→    AddedAt    time.Time    `json:\\\"added_at\\\"`\\n    92→}\\n    93→\\n    94→type BranchStatus string\\n    95→const (\\n    96→    BranchOpen      BranchStatus = \\\"open\\\"\\n    97→    BranchMerged    BranchStatus = \\\"merged\\\"\\n    98→    BranchDiscarded BranchStatus = \\\"discarded\\\"\\n    99→)\\n   100→\\n   101→type PRRef struct {\\n   102→    Number int    `json:\\\"number\\\"`\\n   103→    URL    string `json:\\\"url,omitempty\\\"`\\n   104→}\\n   105→```\\n   106→\\n   107→### CheckpointRef (extended)\\n   108→\\n   109→```go\\n   110→type CheckpointRef struct {\\n   111→    CheckpointID string    `json:\\\"checkpoint_id\\\"`\\n   112→    CommitSHA    string    `json:\\\"commit_sha\\\"`\\n   113→    Summary      string    `json:\\\"summary,omitempty\\\"`\\n   114→    BranchID     string    `json:\\\"branch_id,omitempty\\\"` // links to BranchEntry.ID\\n   115→    CreatedAt    time.Time `json:\\\"created_at\\\"`\\n   116→}\\n   117→```\\n   118→\\n   119→### VerificationEvent\\n   120→\\n   121→```go\\n   122→type VerificationEvent struct {\\n   123→    Kind      string    `json:\\\"kind\\\"`                 // pr_checks, review, security, perf, canary, trail_review, ...\\n   124→    BranchID  string    `json:\\\"branch_id,omitempty\\\"`  // optional — per-branch or per-trail\\n   125→    Status    string    `json:\\\"status\\\"`               // pass, fail, pending, requested, approved, changes_requested\\n   126→    Timestamp time.Time `json:\\\"timestamp\\\"`\\n   127→    Details   string    `json:\\\"details,omitempty\\\"`\\n   128→}\\n   129→```\\n   130→\\n   131→### Trail Status\\n   132→\\n   133→```\\n   134→draft -> active -> validating -> done\\n   135→                       |\\n   136→                   abandoned\\n   137→```\\n   138→\\n   139→- **draft** — intent defined, work hasn't started\\n   140→- **active** — branches exist, work in progress\\n   141→- **validating** — PRs in review, canary running, rollout in progress — all \\\"is this good?\\\"\\n   142→- **done** — intent fully realized and verified (all branches merged/discarded, verifications pass)\\n   143→- **abandoned** — intent dropped\\n   144→\\n   145→\\\"Done\\\" is derived: all branch statuses are terminal (merged or discarded) and at least\\n   146→one is merged, plus verification events are satisfactory. The status field captures the\\n   147→current state; the verification event log captures the evidence.\\n   148→\\n   149→### Trail Review\\n   150→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"25474cc0-fbe2-4bd3-9184-b4a9a218019e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:38:02.416Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a90079da00a244817\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01KBGzztDAkNnBXL2Qi26Q4g\",\"parentToolUs