and existing trail architecture, here are the key findings for implementing multi-branch/multi-PR support:\\n\\n### 1. CHECKPOINT STORE PATTERNS\\n\\n#### Core Data Types (`cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/checkpoint.go`)\\n\\n**CheckpointID & Sharding:**\\n- 12-character hex identifier (same as trail ID format)\\n- Sharded path structure: `<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/`\\n- Example: `a3b2c4d5e6f7` → `a3/b2c4d5e6f7/`\\n\\n**Multi-Session Metadata Structure:**\\n```\\n<checkpoint-id[:2]>/<checkpoint-id[2:]>/\\n├── metadata.json         # CheckpointSummary (aggregated stats)\\n├── 0/                    # First session (0-based indexing)\\n│   ├── metadata.json     # CommittedMetadata (session-specific)\\n│   ├── full.jsonl\\n│   ├── prompt.txt\\n│   └── content_hash.txt\\n├── 1/                    # Second session\\n└── ...\\n```\\n\\n**CheckpointSummary structure** (root-level metadata.json):\\n- `checkpoint_id`: Stable 12-hex identifier\\n- `cli_version`: Version info\\n- `strategy`: Strategy name (\\\"manual-commit\\\")\\n- `branch`: Branch where checkpoint was created\\n- `checkpoints_count`: Total across all sessions\\n- `files_touched`: Merged from all sessions\\n- `sessions`: Array of SessionFilePaths (file paths per session)\\n- `token_usage`: Aggregated token metrics\\n\\n**CommittedMetadata structure** (session-level metadata.json):\\n- `initial_attribution`: Line-level attribution (point-in-time at commit)\\n- `agent`, `model`, `turn_id`: Agent-specific tracking\\n- Session transcript position tracking\\n- Token usage, session metrics, AI-generated summaries\\n\\n#### WriteCommitted Flow (`cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/committed.go`)\\n\\n**Signature:**\\n```go\\nfunc (s *GitStore) WriteCommitted(ctx context.Context, opts WriteCommittedOptions) error\\n```\\n\\n**Write Pattern (lines 46-117):**\\n1. **Validate** checkpoint ID and session ID\\n2. **Ensure branch exists** (`ensureSessionsBranch()`)\\n3. **Get branch ref** (O(1), no flatten): `getSessionsBranchRef()` returns parent