\n\\n**ApplyTreeChanges Function** (alternative for sparse changes):\\n```go\\nfunc ApplyTreeChanges(\\n\\trepo *git.Repository,\\n\\trootTreeHash plumbing.Hash,\\n\\tchanges []TreeChange,  // Path + TreeEntry (nil = delete)\\n) (plumbing.Hash, error)\\n```\\n\\nGroups changes by directory, applies in single recursive pass. Used by shadow branches for file-level modifications.\\n\\n#### BuildTreeFromEntries (`cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/temporary.go:975`)\\n\\n**Signature:**\\n```go\\nfunc BuildTreeFromEntries(\\n\\trepo *git.Repository,\\n\\tentries map[string]object.TreeEntry, // Full paths as keys\\n) (plumbing.Hash, error)\\n```\\n\\n**Implementation:**\\n- Builds tree structure from flattened entries\\n- Creates intermediate directory objects bottom-up\\n- Uses `insertIntoTree()` to recursively place entries\\n- Calls `buildTreeObject()` to create tree objects from bottom up\\n- Returns root tree hash\\n\\n**Used by:**\\n- Trail store initialization (building empty tree for orphan branch)\\n- Checkpoint store session branch creation\\n\\n#### CreateCommit (`committed.go:1498`)\\n\\n**Signature:**\\n```go\\nfunc CreateCommit(\\n\\trepo *git.Repository,\\n\\ttreeHash, parentHash plumbing.Hash,\\n\\tmessage, authorName, authorEmail string,\\n) (plumbing.Hash, error)\\n```\\n\\n**Implementation:**\\n- Creates commit object with tree and parent\\n- Sets author/committer signature with current time\\n- Uses `repo.Storer.NewEncodedObject()` + `SetEncodedObject()`\\n- Returns commit hash\\n\\n**No parent variant:** Pass `plumbing.ZeroHash` for orphan branches (e.g., `entire/trails/v1`)\\n\\n#### Helper Functions\\n\\n**CreateBlobFromContent** (`committed.go`, exported):\\n```go\\nfunc CreateBlobFromContent(repo *git.Repository, content []byte) (plumbing.Hash, error)\\n```\\nCreates blob object and stores it; returns blob hash.\\n\\n**GetGitAuthorFromRepo** (`committed.go`, exported):\\n```go\\nfunc GetGitAuthorFromRepo(repo *git.Repository) (name, email string)\\n```\\nR