it object and extracts TreeHash\\n- Returns `(commitHash, rootTreeHash, error)`\\n\\n**commitAndUpdateRef()** (lines 436-448):\\n- Creates commit with new tree\\n- Uses `SetReference` to update `entire/trails/v1`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. HOOK INTEGRATION PATTERNS\\n\\n#### Post-Commit Hook Flow (`manual_commit_hooks.go`, lines 2374-2384)\\n\\n**appendCheckpointToExistingTrail() function:**\\n```go\\nfunc appendCheckpointToExistingTrail(\\n\\tstore *trail.Store,\\n\\ttrailID trail.ID,\\n\\tcpID id.CheckpointID,\\n\\tcommitSHA plumbing.Hash,\\n\\tprompts []string,\\n) {\\n\\t// Best-effort linking (non-critical)\\n\\tstore.AddCheckpoint(trailID, trail.CheckpointRef{\\n\\t\\tCheckpointID: cpID.String(),\\n\\t\\tCommitSHA:    commitSHA.String(),\\n\\t\\tCreatedAt:    time.Now().UTC(),\\n\\t\\tSummary:      ... // Optional summary\\n\\t})\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Called from PostCommit** (line 1100-1106):\\n```go\\n// Link checkpoint to trail (best-effort)\\nbranchName := GetCurrentBranchName(repo)\\nif branchName != \\\"\\\" && branchName != GetDefaultBranchName(repo) {\\n\\tstore := trail.NewStore(repo)\\n\\texisting, findErr := store.FindByBranch(branchName)\\n\\tif findErr == nil && existing != nil {\\n\\t\\tappendCheckpointToExistingTrail(store, existing.TrailID, result.CheckpointID, head.Hash(), result.Prompts)\\n\\t}\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Key Properties:**\\n- Runs AFTER checkpoint is already written (best-effort)\\n- Errors silently swallowed (trails are non-critical metadata)\\n- Resolves active trail from current branch name\\n- Links checkpoint via `AddCheckpoint()` (which uses `UpdateSubtree` with MergeKeepExisting)\\n\\n#### Prepare-Commit-Msg Hook Pattern (lines 296-497)\\n\\n- **Trailer handling**: Adds `Entire-Checkpoint: <cpID>` trailer if session has new content\\n- **EditInteractive/Template flow**: Adds trailer with comment explaining linkage\\n- **Agent fast-path**: No TTY, directly add trailer\\n- **Amend handling**: Preserves or restores trailer from `LastCheckpointID`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. GO-GIT v6 REFERENCE MANAGEMENT\\n\\n**go-git version used:** `github.com/go-git/go-git/v6 v6.0.0-20260305211659-2083cf940afa`\\n\\n**SetReference Pattern** (used consistently across codebase):\\n```go\\nnewRef := plumbing.NewHashReference(refName, commitHash)\\nif err := s.repo.Storer.SetReference(newRef); err != nil {\\n\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to set branch reference: %w\\\", err)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**No CheckAndSetReference in current codebase:**\\n- Codebase uses only `SetReference` (not atomic CAS)\\n- No optimistic retry loops for concurrent writes\\n- **This is a limitation for multi-branch trails:** concurrent checkpoint writes to same trail from different branches need atomic updates\\n\\n**Key Methods Available:**\\n- `repo.Storer.NewEncodedObject()` - Create new object\\n- `repo.Storer.SetEncodedObject(obj)` - Store object, return hash\\n- `repo.Storer.SetReference(ref)` - Update ref (non-atomic)\\n- `repo.TreeObject(hash)` - Read tree by hash\\n- `repo.CommitObject(hash)` - Read commit by hash\\n- `repo.BlobObject(hash)` - Read blob by hash\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. TRAIL DATA MODEL (Existing)\\n\\n#### Trail.go Types\\n\\n**ID (12-char hex, same as checkpoint ID):**\\n```go\\ntype ID string\\nfunc (id ID) Path() string { return string(id[:2]) + \\\"/\\\" + string(id[2:]) }\\nfunc (id ID) ShardParts() (shard, suffix string)\\n```\\n\\n**Metadata structure:**\\n```go\\ntype Metadata struct {\\n\\tTrailID   ID         `json:\\\"trail_id\\\"`\\n\\tBranch    string     `json:\\\"branch\\\"`        // Current branch name\\n\\tBase      string     `json:\\\"base\\\"`\\n\\tTitle     string     `json:\\\"title\\\"`\\n\\tBody      string     `json:\\\"body\\\"`\\n\\tStatus    Status     `json:\\\"status\\\"`        // draft, open, in_progress, in_review, merged, closed\\n\\tAuthor    string     `json:\\\"author\\\"`\\n\\tAssignees []string   `json:\\\"assignees\\\"`\\n\\tLabels    []string   `json:\\\"labels\\\"`\\n\\tCreatedAt time.Time  `json:\\\"created_at\\\"`\\n\\tUpdatedAt time.Time  `json:\\\"updated_at\\\"`\\n\\tMergedAt  *time.Time `json:\\\"merged_at\\\"`\\n\\tPriority  Priority   `json:\\\"priority,omitempty\\\"`\\n\\tType      Type       `json:\\\"type,omitempty\\\"`\\n\\tReviewers []Reviewer `json:\\\"reviewers,omitempty\\\"`\\n}\\n\\ntype CheckpointRef struct {\\n\\tCheckpointID string    `json:\\\"checkpoint_id\\\"`\\n\\tCommitSHA    string    `json:\\\"commit_sha\\\"`\\n\\tCreatedAt    time.Time `json:\\\"created_at\\\"`\\n\\tSummary      *string   `json:\\\"summary\\\"`\\n}\\n\\ntype Checkpoints struct {\\n\\tCheckpoints []CheckpointRef `json:\\\"checkpoints\\\"`\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 6. KEY PATTERNS FOR MULTI-BRANCH IMPLEMENTATION\\n\\n#### Reference Resolution Pattern\\n**Current:** Single trail per branch via `FindByBranch(branchName)`\\n**For multi-PR:** Need to\\n- Store multiple branch entries per trail (BranchEntry with stable UUID)\\n- Resolve active trail from current branch → find matching BranchEntry in trail → use TrailID\\n- Update trail's BranchEntries array instead of replacing single branch field\\n\\n#### Checkpoint Linking Pattern\\n**Current:** Simple `AddCheckpoint(trailID, ref)` with `MergeKeepExisting`\\n**For multi-branch:** \\n- Include `BranchID` in CheckpointRef to track which branch's work created checkpoint\\n- Use `UpdateSubtree` pattern to append to checkpoints array\\n- Atomic via `SetReference` (but non-atomic if multiple writers)\\n\\n#### Writing Pattern (Non-Atomic CAS Problem)\\n**Current limitation:** No `CheckAndSetReference` in go-git v6\\n**Workaround for concurrent writes:**\\n1. Read current branch ref + tree\\n2. Modify tree (BuildTreeFromEntries or UpdateSubtree)\\n3. Create new commit\\n4. `SetReference` (non-atomic) — race if another process writes concurrently\\n5. If conflict needed: implement retry loop with exponential backoff reading latest ref\\n\\n#### Tree Splicing for Multi-Session/Multi-Branch\\n**Pattern used by checkpoints:**\\n```\\n<checkpoint-id[:2]>/<checkpoint-id[2:]>/\\n├── metadata.json (root, aggregated)\\n├── 0/ (session 0)\\n├── 1/ (session 1)\\n└── ...\\n```\\n\\n**Pattern for multi-branch trails:**\\n```\\n<trail-id[:2]>/<trail-id[2:]>/\\n├── metadata.json (root, aggregated intent)\\n├── branches.json (list of BranchEntry objects with IDs)\\n├── checkpoints.json (list of CheckpointRef with branch_id)\\n├── discussion.json (unified across all branches)\\n└── verification.json (event log across all branches)\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 7. EXISTING DESIGN DOCUMENT\\n\\nLocation: `/docs/plans/2026-03-07-trails-multi-branch-design.md`\\n\\nKey proposed structures:\\n- **BranchEntry:** Stable UUID, branch name, base branch, base commit, status (open/merged/discarded), optional PR ref\\n- **CheckpointRef (extended):** Includes `branch_id` linking to BranchEntry.ID\\n- **VerificationEvent:** Unified event log for all verification types (pr_checks, review, security, perf, canary, trail_review, etc.)\\n- **Intent:** Typed reference with amendments tracking\\n- **Trail Status:** draft → active → validating → done (with abandoned path)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## SUMMARY FOR IMPLEMENTATION\\n\\n### Safe Patterns to Adopt\\n1. **Tree Surgery via UpdateSubtree:** O(depth) modifications with correct sharding\\n2. **MergeKeepExisting mode:** For selective file updates (e.g., AddCheckpoint)\\n3. **ReplaceAll mode:** For full write operations (e.g., trail Write)\\n4. **FlattenTree for reads:** Safe for listing operations\\n5. **SetReference for ref updates:** Sufficient for single-writer workloads (CLI runs serially)\\n\\n### Limitations to Address\\n1. **Non-atomic concurrent writes:** No CheckAndSetReference in go-git v6 — implement retry loop if needed\\n2. **Branch field replacement needed:** Current single `branch` field → array of BranchEntry objects\\n3. **Tree surgery depth:** UpdateSubtree is O(depth) not O(1) — acceptable for reasonable tree structures\\n4. **Metadata migration:** Existing trails with single branch field need migration strategy\\n\\n### File Locations for Implementation\\n- **Checkpoint store helpers:** `/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/committed.go`, `parse_tree.go`, `temporary.go`\\n- **Trail store:** `/cmd/entire/cli/trail/store.go`\\n- **Trail types:** `/cmd/entire/cli/trail/trail.go`\\n- **Hook integration:** `/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` (post-commit linking)\\n- **Design reference:** `/docs/plans/2026-03-07-trails-multi-branch-design.md`\"}],\"totalDurationMs\":102989,\"totalTokens\":107201,\"totalToolUseCount\":38,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":4,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1162,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":101070,\"output_tokens\":4965,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":1162},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"5249531a-7da5-4bfa-b147-909a066baa85\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"7b1a2b36-5fcc-45a8-9f16-39cfb80e7f79\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01MEMCSfVbmeMnuJNfmADM6t\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1/CHANGELOG.md\\n/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1/.claude/skills/test-repo/SKILL.md\\n/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1/docs/plans/2026-02-06-session-phase-state-machine.md\\n/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1/docs/plans/2026-03-07-trails-multi-branch-design.md\\n/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1/docs/plans/2026-02-06-session-phase-state-machine-v2.md\\n/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1/docs/plans/evolve-