1SZG9aW5HSUBeuwU8vYnnyd\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1/docs/plans/2026-03-07-trails-multi-branch-design.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":832,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":71085,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":832,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYnnp9CRNppz9p13ESD3D\",\"uuid\":\"6a4c8fd4-8af5-4d0e-b738-c188aaa53cf7\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"aedad063d2f1713c6\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01KBGzztDAkNnBXL2Qi26Q4g\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01HeeKvjk2B4muesJrGYFm5D\",\"uuid\":\"de7096f9-3206-4e02-b0d8-7eafe61831b5\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:41:44.570Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"de7096f9-3206-4e02-b0d8-7eafe61831b5\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01SZG9aW5HSUBeuwU8vYnnyd\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Trails: Multi-Branch & Multi-PR Support\\n     2→\\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-07\\n     4→**Status:** Draft\\n     5→\\n     6→## Problem\\n     7→\\n     8→Trails currently model a 1:1 relationship between a trail and a branch. Real work\\n     9→often spans multiple branches and PRs: stacked PRs for large features, iterative\\n    10→follow-up PRs, or parallel refactor-then-feature splits. The trail should represent\\n    11→the *intent*, with branches/PRs as execution artifacts serving that intent.\\n    12→\\n    13→## Design Principles\\n    14→\\n    15→- **Trail = intent.** Branches and PRs are mutable execution details.\\n    16→- **Flat list of branches.** No dependency graph — git already encodes branch topology.\\n    17→- **Stateless lookup.** Active trail resolved from current branch, not stored context.\\n    18→- **CAS for concurrency.** Optimistic retry on ref updates, not file splitting.\\n    19→- **Extensible verification.** Unified event log for all verification types.\\n    20→\\n    21→## Data Model\\n    22→\\n    23→### Trail (top-level)\\n    24→\\n    25→```\\n    26→Trail\\n    27→+-- title              (human-friendly label for display)\\n    28→+-- status             (draft | active | validating | done | abandoned)\\n    29→+-- intent             (typed reference — the \\\"what and why\\\")\\n    30→+--   kind             (file, url, issue, inline)\\n    31→+--   value            (path, URL, issue ID, inline text)\\n    32→+--   content          (resolved/cached text)\\n    33→+--   amendments[]     (spec changes with reasoning)\\n    34→+--     description\\n    35→+--     reasoning\\n    36→+--     timestamp\\n    37→+-- branches[]         (execution artifacts — the \\\"how\\\")\\n    38→+--   id               (stable UUID)\\n    39→+--   name             (branch ref, informational — may go stale)\\n    40→+--   base_branch      (target branch name, e.g. \\\"main\\\")\\n    41→+--   base_commit      (fork point SHA, updated on rebase)\\n    42→+--   status           (open | merged | discarded)\\n    43→+--   pr               (optional, replaceable)\\n    44→+--     number\\n    45→+--     url\\n    46→+-- checkpoints[]      (the spine — the \\\"when\\\")\\n    47→+--   checkpoint_id\\n    48→+--   commit_sha\\n    49→+--   summary\\n    50→+--   branch_id        (links to BranchEntry.ID)\\n    51→+--   sessions[]       (contributing agent sessions)\\n    52→+-- verification[]     (event log — unified across all verification types)\\n    53→+--   kind             (pr_checks, review, security, perf, canary,\\n    54→+--                     rollout_stage, trail_review, ...)\\n    55→+--   branch_id        (optional — per-branch or per-trail)\\n    56→+--   status           (pass, fail, pending, requested, approved,\\n    57→+--                     changes_requested)\\n    58→+--   timestamp\\n    59→+--   details\\n    60→+-- discussion[]       (comments/threads — separate file)\\n    61→+-- summary            (aggregated trail-level summary)\\n    62→```\\n    63→\\n    64→### Intent (typed reference)\\n    65→\\n    66→```go\\n    67→type Intent struct {\\n    68→    Kind       string      `json:\\\"kind\\\"`                // file, url, issue, inline\\n    69→    Value      string      `json:\\\"value\\\"`               // path, URL, issue ID, inline text\\n    70→    Content    string      `json:\\\"content,omitempty\\\"`    // resolved intent text (cached)\\n    71→    Amendments []Amendment `json:\\\"amendments,omitempty\\\"`\\n    72→}\\n    73→\\n    74→type Amendment struct {\\n    75→    Description string    `json:\\\"description\\\"`\\n    76→    Reasoning   string    `json:\\\"reasoning\\\"`\\n    77→    Timestamp   time.Time `json:\\\"timestamp\\\"`\\n    78→}\\n    79→```\\n    80→\\n    81→### BranchEntry\\n    82→\\n    83→```go\\n    84→type BranchEntry struct {\\n    85→    ID         string       `json:\\\"id\\\"`                  // stable UUID\\n    86→    Name       string       `json:\\\"name\\\"`                // branch name (informational, may go stale)\\n    87→    BaseBranch string       `json:\\\"base_branch\\\"`         // target branch name\\n    88→    BaseCommit string       `json:\\\"base_commit\\\"`         // fork point SHA\\n    89→    Status     BranchStatus `json:\\\"status\\\"`              // open, merged, discarded\\n    90→    PR         *PRRef       `json:\\\"pr,omitempty\\\"`        // optional, replaceable\\n    91→    AddedAt    time.Time    `json:\\\"added_at\\\"`\\n    92→}\\n    93→\\n    94→type BranchStatus string\\n    95→const (\\n    96→    BranchOpen      BranchStatus = \\\"open\\\"\\n    97→    BranchMerged    BranchStatus = \\\"merged\\\"\\n    98→    BranchDiscarded BranchStatus = \\\"discarded\\\"\\n    99→)\\n   100→\\n   101→type PRRef struct {\\n   102→    Number int    `json:\\\"number\\\"`\\n   103→    URL    string `json:\\\"url,omitempty\\\"`\\n   104→}\\n   105→```\\n   106→\\n   107→### CheckpointRef (extended)\\n   108→\\n   109→```go\\n   110→type CheckpointRef struct {\\n   111→    CheckpointID string    `json:\\\"checkpoint_id\\\"`\\n   112→    CommitSHA    string    `json:\\\"commit_sha\\\"`\\n   113→    Summary      string    `json:\\\"summary,omitempty\\\"`\\n   114→    BranchID     string    `json:\\\"branch_id,omitempty\\\"` // links to BranchEntry.ID\\n   115→    CreatedAt    time.Time `json:\\\"created_at\\\"`\\n   116→}\\n   117→```\\n   118→\\n   119→### VerificationEvent\\n   120→\\n   121→```go\\n   122→type VerificationEvent struct {\\n   123→    Kind      string    `json:\\\"kind\\\"`                 // pr_checks, review, security, perf, canary, trail_review, ...\\n   124→    BranchID  string    `json:\\\"branch_id,omitempty\\\"`  // optional — per-branch or per-trail\\n   125→    Status    string    `json:\\\"status\\\"`               // pass, fail, pending, requested, approved, changes_requested\\n   126→    Timestamp time.Time `json:\\\"timestamp\\\"`\\n   127→    Details   string    `json:\\\"details,omitempty\\\"`\\n   128→}\\n   129→```\\n   130→\\n   131→### Trail Status\\n   132→\\n   133→```\\n   134→draft -> active -> validating -> done\\n   135→                       |\\n   136→                   abandoned\\n   137→```\\n   138→\\n   139→- **draft** — intent defined, work hasn't started\\n   140→- **active** — branches exist, work in progress\\n   141→- **validating** — PRs in review, canary running, rollout in progress — all \\\"is this good?\\\"\\n   142→- **done** — intent fully realized and verified (all branches merged/discarded, verifications pass)\\n   143→- **abandoned** — intent dropped\\n   144→\\n   145→\\\"Done\\\" is derived: all branch statuses are terminal (merged or discarded) and at least\\n   146→one is merged, plus verification events are satisfactory. The status field captures the\\n   147→current state; the verification event log captures the evidence.\\n   148→\\n   149→### Trail Review\\n   150→\\n   151→Trail review is a verification event, not a status. It can happen at any point in the\\n   152→lifecycle (design review before coding, checkpoint review mid-feature, final review\\n   153→before rollout). Signaling mechanism TBD — rules/policies on top of the verification\\n   154→event log.\\n   155→\\n   156→```\\n   157→verification event:\\n   158→  kind: \\\"trail_review\\\"\\n   159→  status: \\\"requested\\\" | \\\"approved\\\" | \\\"changes_requested\\\"\\n   160→```\\n   161→\\n   162→## Storage Layout\\n   163→\\n   164→On `entire/trails/v1` orphan branch, sharded by trail ID:\\n   165→\\n   166→```\\n   167→<trail-id[:2]>/<trail-id[2:]>/\\n   168→+-- metadata.json       (title, status, intent, branches, summary)\\n   169→+-- checkpoints.json    (checkpoint refs with branch_id)\\n   170→+-- verification.json   (verification event log)\\n   171→+-- discussion.json     (comments/threads)\\n   172→```\\n   173→\\n   174→Single `metadata.json` per trail. CAS retry handles concurrent writes — no need for\\n   175→file splitting or subdirectories.\\n   176→\\n   177→## Concurrency: CAS Ref Updates\\n   178→\\n   179→The codebase currently uses unconditional `SetReference` for all ref updates. This\\n   180→is a race condition when two sessions write concurrently to the same orphan branch\\n   181→(e.g., two worktrees appending checkpoints to the same trail).\\n   182→\\n   183→**Fix:** Use go-git's `CheckAndSetReference(new, old)` for CAS semantics.\\n   184→\\n   185→```go\\n   186→// Write loop with optimistic retry\\n   187→for {\\n   188→    tipHash, rootTree := readBranchTip()    // step 1: read\\n   189→    newTree := applyChanges(rootTree)        // step 2: modify\\n   190→    newCommit := createCommit(newTree, tipHash)\\n   191→    err := repo.Storer.CheckAndSetReference(\\n   192→        plumbing.NewHashReference(refName, newCommit),\\n   193→        plumbing.NewHashReference(refName, tipHash),  // expected old value\\n   194→    )\\n   195→    if err == nil {\\n   196→        break // success\\n   197→    }\\n   198→    // ref moved — retry from step 1\\n   199→}\\n   200→```\\n   201→\\n   202→This is a foundational improvement that benefits all orphan branch writes (trails,\\n   203→checkpoints, metadata), not just multi-branch trails.\\n   204→\\n   205→## Trail Context Resolution (Stateless)\\n   206→\\n   207→No stored \\\"active trail\\\" context. Resolved fresh on every command:\\n   208→\\n   209→1. **`--trail <id>` flag** — explicit, always wins\\n   210→2. **Branch lookup** — current branch found in exactly one trail's `Branches[]`\\n   211→3. **No match / ambiguous** — prompt or error\\n   212→\\n   213→This avoids stale context when switching branches within a worktree. The cost is a\\n   214→branch-to-trail scan on every command, which is acceptable at expected scale.\\n   215→\\n   216→## CLI Commands\\n   217→\\n   218→### Trail creation (modified)\\n   219→\\n   220→```bash\\n   221→entire trail create \\\"Add auth system\\\"\\n   222→entire trail create \\\"Add auth system\\\" --intent-file docs/spec.md\\n   223→entire trail create \\\"Add auth system\\\" --intent-issue LIN-123\\n   224→entire trail create \\\"Add auth system\\\" --intent \\\"inline description\\\"\\n   225→```\\n   226→\\n   227→Creates the trail and auto-adds the current branch as the first branch entry.\\n   228→\\n   229→### Branch management (new)\\n   230→\\n   231→```bash\\n   232→entire trail branch add                           # add current branch to active trail\\n   233→entire trail branch add feature/auth-api          # add named branch\\n   234→entire trail branch add --base feature/auth-core  # explicit base (stacking)\\n   235→entire trail branch set-pr 43                     # set/replace PR on current branch\\n   236→entire trail branch set-pr 43 --branch feature/x  # set PR on named branch\\n   237→entire trail branch discard                       # mark current branch as discarded\\n   238→```\\n   239→\\n   240→Trail resolution uses stateless lookup (see above). If current branch isn't in a\\n   241→trail, `--trail <id>` is required or an interactive picker is shown.\\n   242→\\n   243→### Viewing (modified)\\n   244→\\n   245→```bash\\n   246→entire trail show                                 # full trail view with all branches\\n   247→entire trail list                                 # list trails\\n   248→```\\n   249→\\n   250→### Verification (future)\\n   251→\\n   252→```bash\\n   253→entire trail verify request                       # request trail review\\n   254→entire trail verify approve                       # approve trail review\\n   255→```\\n   256→\\n   257→## Hook Integration\\n   258→\\n   259→### Post-commit checkpoint linking\\n   260→\\n   261→Current flow:\\n   262→1. Post-commit fires\\n   263→2. Get current branch name\\n   264→3. `store.FindByBranch(branchName)` -> finds trail\\n   265→4. Append checkpoint to trail\\n   266→\\n   267→New flow:\\n   268→1. Post-commit fires\\n   269→2. Get current branch name\\n   270→3. `store.FindByBranch(branchName)` -> returns `(trail, branchEntry)`\\n   271→4. Append checkpoint with `branch_id: branchEntry.ID`\\n   272→5. Write with CAS retry\\n   273→\\n   274→`FindByBranch` scans all trails' `Branches[]` fields. Returns matched\\n   275→`BranchEntry` alongside the trail. Warns (logs) if branch appears in multiple\\n   276→trails; uses first match.\\n   277→\\n   278→Branches not in any trail: checkpoint still saved to shadow branch and condensed\\n   279→to `entire/checkpoints/v1`. Trail linkage is optional/additive.\\n   280→\\n   281→## Migration\\n   282→\\n   283→No migration of existing trails. Old trails stay as-is on `entire/trails/v1`.\\n   284→New trails use the new schema. Read path handles both formats (presence/absence\\n   285→of `branches` field).\\n   286→\\n   287→## Not In Scope\\n   288→\\n   289→- Automatic branch detection (no git checkout hook available)\\n   290→- Dependency graph between branches (git topology suffices)\\n   291→- GitHub/Linear PR integration (future — PR number is stored, sync is separate)\\n   292→- Deployment verification events (canary, rollout — structure supports it, implementation later)\\n   293→- Trail review signaling UX (policy layer TBD)\\n   294→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"6fc080cd-bd70-427f-9c24-7451aad83d87\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:41:44.587Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"aedad063d2f1713c6\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01KBGzztDAkNnBXL2Qi26Q4g\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01HeeKvjk2B4muesJrGYFm5D\",\"uuid\":\"5a45607c-93a5-4a1b-b381-8626ec3ea658\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:41:44.594Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"5a45607c-93a5-4a1b-b381-8626ec3ea658\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:41:46.560Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01XbdqVQne77eBkrYS9gkUnv\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_015PXZHZqBPAfNWQa8HC7jcJ\",\"name\":\"Bash\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"grep -n \\\"PushTrailsBranch\\\" /Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/*.go\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":0,\"cach