ation (manual_commit_hooks.go)**\\n\\n#### **Key Functions**\\n- `appendCheckpointToExistingTrail(store *trail.Store, trailID ID, cpID id.CheckpointID, commitSHA plumbing.Hash, prompts []string)` at line 2376\\n  - Creates checkpoint reference with summary from prompts\\n  - Calls `store.AddCheckpoint()` (best-effort, non-critical)\\n\\n#### **Post-Commit Trail Linking** (lines 1100-1108)\\n```go\\nbranchName := GetCurrentBranchName(repo)\\nif branchName != \\\"\\\" && branchName != GetDefaultBranchName(repo) {\\n    store := trail.NewStore(repo)\\n    existing, findErr := store.FindByBranch(branchName)  // <-- KEY LINE\\n    if findErr == nil && existing != nil {\\n        appendCheckpointToExistingTrail(store, existing.TrailID, result.CheckpointID, head.Hash(), result.Prompts)\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**How it works:**\\n1. Gets current branch name from repo\\n2. Calls `store.FindByBranch(branchName)` to look up trail\\n3. If trail found, appends checkpoint with branch context\\n4. **Silent on error** — trails are non-critical metadata\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **Import Paths Used**\\n\\n**In trail package:**\\n```go\\nimport (\\n    \\\"crypto/rand\\\"\\n    \\\"encoding/hex\\\"\\n    \\\"encoding/json\\\"\\n    \\\"errors\\\"\\n    \\\"fmt\\\"\\n    \\\"regexp\\\"\\n    \\\"strings\\\"\\n    \\\"time\\\"\\n    \\n    \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint\\\"\\n    \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/paths\\\"\\n    \\n    \\\"github.com/go-git/go-git/v6\\\"\\n    \\\"github.com/go-git/go-git/v6/plumbing\\\"\\n    \\\"github.com/go-git/go-git/v6/plumbing/filemode\\\"\\n    \\\"github.com/go-git/go-git/v6/plumbing/object\\\"\\n)\\n```\\n\\n**Constants from paths package:**\\n- `paths.TrailsBranchName = \\\"entire/trails/v1\\\"`\\n\\n**Helper functions from checkpoint package:**\\n- `BuildTreeFromEntries(repo, entries)`\\n- `GetGitAuthorFromRepo(repo)` → (name, email)\\n- `CreateCommit(repo, treeHash, parentHash, message, name, email)` → hash\\n- `Crea