ork point SHA\\n    Status     BranchStatus // open, merged, discarded\\n    PR         *PRRef       // optional, replaceable\\n    AddedAt    time.Time\\n}\\n\\ntype Intent struct {\\n    Kind       string        // file, url, issue, inline\\n    Value      string        // path, URL, issue ID, text\\n    Content    string        // resolved/cached\\n    Amendments []Amendment\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Key changes for multi-branch:**\\n1. **FindByBranch** will scan all trails' `Branches[]` arrays and return matched `BranchEntry`\\n2. **CAS semantics** — use `CheckAndSetReference(new, old)` for concurrent writes\\n3. **Stateless lookup** — resolve trail from current branch, no stored context\\n4. **Checkpoint branch tracking** — add `BranchID` to `CheckpointRef`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### **Related Checkpoint ID Type**\\n\\nIn `/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/id/id.go`:\\n```go\\ntype CheckpointID string\\nconst Pattern = `[0-9a-f]{12}`  // same 12-hex format as trail.ID\\n\\n// Functions:\\nGenerate() (CheckpointID, error)\\nValidate(s string) error\\n(id CheckpointID) Path() string  // returns \\\"a3/b2c4d5e6f7\\\"\\n```\\n\\nCheckpointID is used interchangeably with trail.ID — both are 12-hex identifiers with same sharding scheme.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Summary for Implementation Planning\\n\\n**Current state (1:1 branch:trail):**\\n- `Metadata.Branch` field stores single branch name\\n- `FindByBranch(branchName)` scans all metadata for exact match\\n- Post-commit hook links checkpoints via current branch lookup\\n- No concurrent write protection (unconditional SetReference)\\n\\n**Multi-branch target state:**\\n- `Metadata.Branches` array stores `BranchEntry` objects\\n- `FindByBranch()` scans all trails' branch arrays, returns matched entry\\n- CheckpointRef includes `BranchID` to link to specific branch in trail\\n- CAS retry loop for safe concurrent updates\\n- Trail context resolved stateless from current branch, no stored context\\n\\n**Key files t