`docs/plans/2026-03-07-trails-multi-branch-design.md`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Task 1: New Types in trail.go\\n\\nAdd `Intent`, `Amendment`, `BranchEntry`, `BranchStatus`, `PRRef`, `VerificationEvent` types and update `Status` constants.\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/trail/trail.go`\\n- Test: `cmd/entire/cli/trail/trail_test.go`\\n\\n**Step 1: Write tests for new status constants**\\n\\n```go\\n// In trail_test.go, add:\\n\\nfunc TestNewStatusConstants(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\n\\t// New statuses should be valid\\n\\tfor _, s := range []Status{StatusDraft, StatusActive, StatusValidating, StatusDone, StatusAbandoned} {\\n\\t\\tif !s.IsValid() {\\n\\t\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"status %q should be valid\\\", s)\\n\\t\\t}\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\t// Old statuses removed\\n\\tfor _, s := range []Status{\\\"open\\\", \\\"in_progress\\\", \\\"in_review\\\", \\\"merged\\\", \\\"closed\\\"} {\\n\\t\\tif s.IsValid() {\\n\\t\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"old status %q should no longer be valid\\\", s)\\n\\t\\t}\\n\\t}\\n}\\n\\nfunc TestBranchStatus_IsValid(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\n\\tvalid := []BranchStatus{BranchOpen, BranchMerged, BranchDiscarded}\\n\\tfor _, s := range valid {\\n\\t\\tif !s.IsValid() {\\n\\t\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"branch status %q should be valid\\\", s)\\n\\t\\t}\\n\\t}\\n\\tif BranchStatus(\\\"invalid\\\").IsValid() {\\n\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"invalid branch status should not be valid\\\")\\n\\t}\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\\n\\nRun: `cd /Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1 && go test ./cmd/entire/cli/trail/ -run \\\"TestNewStatusConstants|TestBranchStatus_IsValid\\\" -v`\\nExpected: FAIL — `StatusActive`, `StatusValidating`, etc. not defined\\n\\n**Step 3: Add new types to trail.go**\\n\\nReplace the existing `Status` constants block and add new types after the `Reviewer` struct:\\n\\n```go\\n// Status constants — replace existing block\\nconst (\\n\\tStatusDraft      Status = \\\"draft\\\"\\n\\tStatusActive     Status = \\\"active\\\"\\n\\tStatusValidating Status = \\\"validating\\\"\\n\\tStatusDone       Status = \\\"done\\\"\\n\\tStatusAbandoned  Status = \\\"abandoned\\\"\\n)\\n\\nfunc ValidStatuses() []Status {\\n\\treturn []Status{\\n\\t\\tStatusDraft,\\n\\t\\tStatusActive,\\n\\t\\tStatusValidating,\\n\\t\\tStatusDone,\\n\\t\\tStatusAbandoned,\\n\\t}\\n}\\n```\\n\\nAdd new types after the `Reviewer` struct (before `Metadata`):\\n\\n```go\\n// BranchStatus represents the lifecycle status of a branch within a trail.\\ntype BranchStatus string\\n\\nconst (\\n\\tBranchOpen      BranchStatus = \\\"open\\\"\\n\\tBranchMerged    BranchStatus = \\\"merged\\\"\\n\\tBranchDiscarded BranchStatus = \\\"discarded\\\"\\n)\\n\\n// IsValid returns true if the branch status is recognized.\\nfunc (s BranchStatus) IsValid() bool {\\n\\tswitch s {\\n\\tcase BranchOpen, BranchMerged, BranchDiscarded:\\n\\t\\treturn true\\n\\t}\\n\\treturn false\\n}\\n\\n// Intent is a typed reference to the work's purpose — a spec file, issue, URL, or inline text.\\ntype Intent struct {\\n\\tKind       string      `json:\\\"kind\\\"`                // file, url, issue, inline\\n\\tValue      string      `json:\\\"value\\\"`               // path, URL, issue ID, inline text\\n\\tContent    string      `json:\\\"content,omitempty\\\"`    // resolved intent text (cached)\\n\\tAmendments []Amendment `json:\\\"amendments,omitempty\\\"`\\n}\\n\\n// Amendment records a change to the intent with reasoning.\\ntype Amendment struct {\\n\\tDescription string    `json:\\\"description\\\"`\\n\\tReasoning   string    `json:\\\"reasoning\\\"`\\n\\tTimestamp   time.Time `json:\\\"timestamp\\\"`\\n}\\n\\n// BranchEntry tracks a branch serving a trail's intent.\\ntype BranchEntry struct {\\n\\tID         string       `json:\\\"id\\\"`\\n\\tName       string       `json:\\\"name\\\"`\\n\\tBaseBranch string       `json:\\\"base_branch\\\"`\\n\\tBaseCommit string       `json:\\\"base_commit,omitempty\\\"`\\n\\tStatus     BranchStatus `json:\\\"status\\\"`\\n\\tPR         *PRRef       `json:\\\"pr,omitempty\\\"`\\n\\tAddedAt    time.Time    `json:\\\"added_at\\\"`\\n}\\n\\n// PRRef is a replaceable reference to a pull request.\\ntype PRRef struct {\\n\\tNumber int    `json:\\\"number\\\"`\\n\\tURL    string `json:\\\"url,omitempty\\\"`\\n}\\n\\n// VerificationEvent records a verification action on a trail or branch.\\ntype VerificationEvent struct {\\n\\tKind      string    `json:\\\"kind\\\"`\\n\\tBranchID  string    `json:\\\"branch_id,omitempty\\\"`\\n\\tStatus    string    `json:\\\"status\\\"`\\n\\tTimestamp time.Time `json:\\\"timestamp\\\"`\\n\\tDetails   string    `json:\\\"details,omitempty\\\"`\\n}\\n\\n// Verification holds the list of verification events for a trail.\\ntype Verification struct {\\n\\tEvents []VerificationEvent `json:\\\"events\\\"`\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Step 4: Run tests to verify they pass**\\n\\nRun: `cd /Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1 && go test ./cmd/entire/cli/trail/ -run \\\"TestNewStatusConstants|TestBranchStatus_IsValid\\\" -v`\\nExpected: PASS\\n\\n**Step 5: Commit**\\n\\n```bash\\ngit add cmd/entire/cli/trail/trail.go cmd/entire/cli/trail/trail_test.go\\ngit commit -m \\\"trail: add Intent, BranchEntry, VerificationEvent types and new status constants\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Task 2: Update Metadata Struct\\n\\nReplace single `Branch`/`Base` fields with `Branches[]`, add `Intent` and `Summary` fields. Keep old fields with `json` tags for backward-compat reads but mark deprecated.\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/trail/trail.go`\\n- Test: `cmd/entire/cli/trail/trail_test.go`\\n\\n**Step 1: Write test for new Metadata fields**\\n\\n```go\\nfunc TestMetadata_WithBranches(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\n\\tnow := time.Now().Truncate(time.Second)\\n\\tm := &Metadata{\\n\\t\\tTrailID: \\\"a1b2c3d4e5f6\\\",\\n\\t\\tTitle:   \\\"Add auth\\\",\\n\\t\\tStatus:  StatusActive,\\n\\t\\tIntent: &Intent{\\n\\t\\t\\tKind:  \\\"inline\\\",\\n\\t\\t\\tValue: \\\"Add