:{\"messageId\":\"df394625-ec4a-4f24-b91a-13515e24f9d3\",\"trackedFileBackups\":{\"docs/plans/2026-03-07-trails-multi-branch-design.md\":{\"backupFileName\":null,\"version\":1,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-07T00:36:23.783Z\"},\"docs/plans/2026-03-07-trails-multi-branch-plan.md\":{\"backupFileName\":null,\"version\":1,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-07T02:49:25.805Z\"}},\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:35:03.738Z\"},\"isSnapshotUpdate\":true}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"3e5ca61a-5d4b-42b6-bad0-4636db122079\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Write\",\"command\":\"callback\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01PvLZZRt5oC59QpFjAQ8xbM\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01PvLZZRt5oC59QpFjAQ8xbM\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T02:49:25.808Z\",\"uuid\":\"c376dbbf-c97e-4b06-bc3d-3e78293033f5\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"3e5ca61a-5d4b-42b6-bad0-4636db122079\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"cc5ed6bd-0c2c-4c91-94f7-7c18e3bda941\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/trails-multi-pr\",\"slug\":\"jazzy-inventing-fern\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01PvLZZRt5oC59QpFjAQ8xbM\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"File created successfully at: /Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1/docs/plans/2026-03-07-trails-multi-branch-plan.md\"}]},\"uuid\":\"3f60d727-add2-4838-9697-6aa83bf2f22a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T02:49:25.807Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"create\",\"filePath\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1/docs/plans/2026-03-07-trails-multi-branch-plan.md\",\"content\":\"# Trails Multi-Branch Implementation Plan\\n\\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\\n\\n**Goal:** Evolve trails from single-branch to multi-branch, supporting stacked PRs, iterative follow-ups, and parallel branch workflows.\\n\\n**Architecture:** Add `Intent`, `BranchEntry`, `VerificationEvent` types to the trail domain model. Replace single `Branch`/`Base` fields with a `Branches[]` array. Update `FindByBranch` to scan branch arrays. Add CAS retry to trail store writes. Add `entire trail branch` CLI subcommands.\\n\\n**Tech Stack:** Go, go-git v6, cobra, huh (forms)\\n\\n**Design Doc:** `docs/plans/2026-03-07-trails-multi-branch-design.md`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Task 1: New Types in trail.go\\n\\nAdd `Intent`, `Amendment`, `BranchEntry`, `BranchStatus`, `PRRef`, `VerificationEvent` types and update `Status` constants.\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/trail/trail.go`\\n- Test: `cmd/entire/cli/trail/trail_test.go`\\n\\n**Step 1: Write tests for new status constants**\\n\\n```go\\n// In trail_test.go, add:\\n\\nfunc TestNewStatusConstants(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\n\\t// New statuses should be valid\\n\\tfor _, s := range []Status{StatusDraft, StatusActive, StatusValidating, StatusDone, StatusAbandoned} {\\n\\t\\tif !s.IsValid() {\\n\\t\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"status %q should be valid\\\", s)\\n\\t\\t}\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\t// Old statuses removed\\n\\tfor _, s := range []Status{\\\"open\\\", \\\"in_progress\\\", \\\"in_review\\\", \\\"merged\\\", \\\"closed\\\"} {\\n\\t\\tif s.IsValid() {\\n\\t\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"old status %q should no longer be valid\\\", s)\\n\\t\\t}\\n\\t}\\n}\\n\\nfunc TestBranchStatus_IsValid(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\n\\tvalid := []BranchStatus{BranchOpen, BranchMerged, BranchDiscarded}\\n\\tfor _, s := range valid {\\n\\t\\tif !s.IsValid() {\\n\\t\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"branch status %q should be valid\\\", s)\\n\\t\\t}\\n\\t}\\n\\tif BranchStatus(\\\"invalid\\\").IsValid() {\\n\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"invalid branch status should not be valid\\\")\\n\\t}\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\\n\\nRun: `cd /Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1 && go test ./cmd/entire/cli/trail/ -run \\\"TestNewStatusConstants|TestBranchStatus_IsValid\\\" -v`\\nExpected: FAIL — `StatusActive`, `StatusValidating`, etc. not defined\\n\\n**Step 3: Add new types to trail.go**\\n\\nReplace the existing `Status` constants block and add new types after the `Reviewer` struct:\\n\\n```go\\n// Status constants — replace existing block\\nconst (\\n\\tStatusDraft      Status = \\\"draft\\\"\\n\\tStatusActive     Status = \\\"active\\\"\\n\\tStatusValidating Status = \\\"validating\\\"\\n\\tStatusDone       Status = \\\"done\\\"\\n\\tStatusAbandoned  Status = \\\"abandoned\\\"\\n)\\n\\nfunc ValidStatuses() []Status {\\n\\treturn []Status{\\n\\t\\tStatusDraft,\\n\\t\\tStatusActive,\\n\\t\\tStatusValidating,\\n\\t\\tStatusDone,\\n\\t\\tStatusAbandoned,\\n\\t}\\n}\\n```\\n\\nAdd new types after the `Reviewer` struct (before `Metadata`):\\n\\n```go\\n// BranchStatus represents the lifecycle status of a branch within a trail.\\ntype BranchStatus string\\n\\nconst (\\n\\tBranchOpen      BranchStatus = \\\"open\\\"\\n\\tBranchMerged    BranchStatus = \\\"merged\\\"\\n\\tBranchDiscarded BranchStatus = \\\"discarded\\\"\\n)\\n\\n// IsValid returns true if the branch status is recognized.\\nfunc (s BranchStatus) IsValid() bool {\\n\\tswitch s {\\n\\tcase BranchOpen, BranchMerged, BranchDiscarded:\\n\\t\\treturn true\\n\\t}\\n\\treturn false\\n}\\n\\n// Intent is a typed reference to the work's purpose — a spec file, issue, URL, or inline text.\\ntype Intent struct {\\n\\tKind       string      `json:\\\"kind\\\"`                // file, url, issue, inline\\n\\tValue      string      `json:\\\"value\\\"`               // path, URL, issue ID, inline text\\n\\tContent    string      `json:\\\"content,omitempty\\\"`    // resolved intent text (cached)\\n\\tAmendments []Amendment `json:\\\"amendments,omitempty\\\"`\\n}\\n\\n// Amendment records a change to the intent with reasoning.\\ntype Amendment struct {\\n\\tDescription string    `json:\\\"description\\\"`\\n\\tReasoning   string    `json:\\\"reasoning\\\"`\\n\\tTimestamp   time.Time `json:\\\"timestamp\\\"`\\n}\\n\\n// BranchEntry tracks a branch serving a trail's intent.\\ntype BranchEntry struct {\\n\\tID         string       `json:\\\"id\\\"`\\n\\tName       string       `json:\\\"name\\\"`\\n\\tBaseBranch string       `json:\\\"base_branch\\\"`\\n\\tBaseCommit string       `json:\\\"base_commit,omitempty\\\"`\\n\\tStatus     BranchStatus `json:\\\"status\\\"`\\n\\tPR         *PRRef       `json:\\\"pr,omitempty\\\"`\\n\\tAddedAt    time.Time    `json:\\\"added_at\\\"`\\n}\\n\\n// PRRef is a replaceable reference to a pull request.\\ntype PRRef struct {\\n\\tNumber int    `json:\\\"number\\\"`\\n\\tURL    string `json:\\\"url,omitempty\\\"`\\n}\\n\\n// VerificationEvent records a verification action on a trail or branch.\\ntype VerificationEvent struct {\\n\\tKind      string    `json:\\\"kind\\\"`\\n\\tBranchID  string    `json:\\\"branch_id,omitempty\\\"`\\n\\tStatus    string    `json:\\\"status\\\"`\\n\\tTimestamp time.Time `json:\\\"timestamp\\\"`\\n\\tDetails   string    `json:\\\"details,omitempty\\\"`\\n}\\n\\n// Verification holds the list of verification events for a trail.\\ntype Verification struct {\\n\\tEvents []VerificationEvent `json:\\\"events\\\"`\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Step 4: Run tests to verify they pass**\\n\\nRun: `cd /Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1 && go test ./cmd/entire/cli/trail/ -run \\\"TestNewStatusConstants|TestBranchStatus_IsValid\\\" -v`\\nExpected: PASS\\n\\n**Step 5: Commit**\\n\\n```bash\\ngit add cmd/entire/cli/trail/trail.go cmd/entire/cli/trail/trail_test.go\\ngit commit -m \\\"trail: add Intent, BranchEntry, VerificationEvent types and new status constants\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Task 2: Update Metadata Struct\\n\\nReplace single `Branch`/`Base` fields with `Branches[]`, add `Intent` and `Summary` fields. Keep old fields with `json` tags for backward-compat reads but mark deprecated.\\n\\n**Files:**\\n- Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/trail/trail.go`\\n- Test: `cmd/entire/cli/trail/trail_test.go`\\n\\n**Step 1: Write test for new Metadata fields**\\n\\n```go\\nfunc TestMetadata_WithBranches(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\n\\tnow := time.Now().Truncate(time.Second)\\n\\tm := &Metadata{\\n\\t\\tTrailID: \\\"a1b2c3d4e5f6\\\",\\n\\t\\tTitle:   \\\"Add auth\\\",\\n\\t\\tStatus:  StatusActive,\\n\\t\\tIntent: &Intent{\\n\\t\\t\\tKind:  \\\"inline\\\",\\n\\t\\t\\tValue: \\\"Add authentication to the API\\\",\\n\\t\\t},\\n\\t\\tBranches: []BranchEntry{\\n\\t\\t\\t{\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tID:         \\\"uuid-1\\\",\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tName:       \\\"feature/auth-core\\\",\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tBaseBranch: \\\"main\\\",\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tStatus:     BranchOpen,\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tAddedAt:    now,\\n\\t\\t\\t},\\n\\t\\t\\t{\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tID:         \\\"uuid-2\\\",\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tName:       \\\"feature/auth-api\\\",\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tBaseBranch: \\\"feature/auth-core\\\",\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tStatus:     BranchOpen,\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tPR:         &PRRef{Number: 42, URL: \\\"https://github.com/org/repo/pull/42\\\"},\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tAddedAt:    now,\\n\\t\\t\\t},\\n\\t\\t},\\n\\t\\tCreatedAt: now,\\n\\t\\tUpdatedAt: now,\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\tif len(m.Branches) != 2 {\\n\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"expected 2 branches, got %d\\\", len(m.Branches))\\n\\t}\\n\\tif m.Branches[1].PR == nil || m.Branches[1].PR.Number != 42 {\\n\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"expected PR number 42 on second branch\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\tif m.Intent == nil || m.Intent.Kind != \\\"inline\\\" {\\n\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"expected inline intent\\\")\\n\\t}\\n}\\n\\nfunc TestMetadata_FindBranch(t *testing.T) {\\n\\tt.Parallel()\\n\\n\\tm := &Metadata{\\n\\t\\tTrailID: \\\"a1b2c3d4e5f6\\\",\\n\\t\\tBranches: []BranchEntry{\\n\\t\\t\\t{ID: \\\"uuid-1\\\", Name: \\\"feature/auth-core\\\"},\\n\\t\\t\\t{ID: \\\"uuid-2\\\", Name: \\\"feature/auth-api\\\"},\\n\\t\\t},\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\tentry := m.FindBranch(\\\"feature/auth-api\\\")\\n\\tif entry == nil {\\n\\t\\tt.Fatal(\\\"expected to find branch\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\tif entry.ID != \\\"uuid-2\\\" {\\n\\t\\tt.Errorf(\\\"expected uuid-2, got %s\\\", entry.ID)\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\tif m.FindBranch(\\\"nonexistent\\\") != nil {\\n\\t\\tt.Error(\\\"expected nil for nonexistent branch\\\")\\n\\t}\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\\n\\nRun: `cd /Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1 && go test ./cmd/entire/cli/trail/ -run \\\"TestMetadata_WithBranches|TestMetadata_FindBranch\\\" -v`\\nExpected: FAIL — `Branches` field and `FindBranch` method not defined\\n\\n**Step 3: Update Metadata struct in trail.go**\\n\\n```go\\ntype Metadata struct {\\n\\tTrailID   ID         `json:\\\"trail_id\\\"`\\n\\tTitle     string     `json:\\\"title\\\"`\\n\\tBody      string     `json:\\\"body\\\"`\\n\\tStatus    Status     `json:\\\"status\\\"`\\n\\tAuthor    string     `json:\\\"author\\\"`\\n\\tAssignees []string   `json:\\\"assignees\\\"`\\n\\tLabels    []string   `json:\\\"labels\\\"`\\n\\tCreatedAt time.Time  `json:\\\"created_at\\\"`\\n\\tUpdatedAt time.Time  `json:\\\"updated_at\\\"`\\n\\tMergedAt  *time.Time `json:\\\"merged_at,omitempty\\\"`\\n\\tPriority  Priority   `json:\\\"priority,omitempty\\\"`\\n\\tType      Type       `json:\\\"type,omitempty\\\"`\\n\\tReviewers []Reviewer `json:\\\"reviewers,omitempty\\\"`\\n\\n\\t// Multi-branch fields (new)\\n\\tIntent   *Intent        `json:\\\"intent,omitempty\\\"`\\n\\tBranches []BranchEntry  `json:\\\"branches,omitempty\\\"`\\n\\tSummary  string         `json:\\\"summary,omitempty\\\"`\\n\\n\\t// Legacy single-branch fields (kept for backward compat reads)\\n\\tBranch string `json:\\\"branch,omitempty\\\"`\\n\\tBase   string `json:\\\"base,omitempty\\\"`\\n}\\n\\n// FindBranch returns the BranchEntry matching the given branch name, or nil.\\nfunc (m *Metadata) FindBranch(branchName string) *BranchEntry {\\n\\tfor i := range m.Branches {\\n\\t\\tif m.Branches[